          The leg structure design was inspired by spacecraft landers, which can be seen in the shape created by the two structures flanking the central printer and the printer itself. <br> <br>

          Each leg structure stands 5 feet tall and supports a pair of interactive touchscreens. The structures are designed to make use of additive manufacturing, including the usage of topology optimization to add visual interest and provide a learning opportunity to showcase what additive manufacturing can create, even on a large scale.

          <div class="w3-xxlarge cm-h1">
            Techniques Used
          </div>
          <button class="w3-button cm-button" onclick="expand('topo')">Topology Optimization</button>
          <br>
          <div id="topo" class="w3-container w3-hide">
            <div class="w3-cell-row w3-center">
