              <div class="w3-cell">
                <img class="w3-image" src="static/panel_opt3.png" alt="" style="max-height:400px;">
              </div>
            </div>
            Topology optimization is the process of minimizing the material required to satisfy a set of loading conditions. The result is a reduction of weight and material waste while also decreasing manufacturing time. Additive manufacturing enables the production of designs created using topology optimization. The patterns used for this structure were created using a variety of loading conditions beyond those strictly required for the structure, and evaluated by potential users for their visual appeal and perceived stability. Users preferred the patterns that are more symmetric in both vertical and horizontal directions, leading to the selection above of panels to be used in each leg structure.
